The paper discusses agent-based approaches for solving a combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of ant-based models suggests a focus on Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Robotics (cs.RO). The problem also involves graph partitioning, which is a topic in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of agent-based approaches for optimization suggests a connection to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
